esqlQuery.esql:
// Alert when Kubernetes nodes report memory pressure.
//
// What triggers this alert:
// Node memory_pressure=true — kernel OOM killer may start killing processes.
//
// Common causes:
// Memory leaks, oversized workloads, insufficient node memory, no resource limits.
//
// Action needed:
// Check node memory usage, review pod resource limits, scale cluster.
//
// To scope to a cluster, add: AND `orchestrator.cluster.name` == "YOUR_CLUSTER"
TS metrics-kubernetes.node-*
| WHERE `kubernetes.node.status.memory_pressure` == "true"
| STATS doc_count = COUNT(*)
  BY `orchestrator.cluster.name`, `kubernetes.node.name`
| WHERE doc_count > 0
